        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>
                <date>Sept. 6. 1845</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your two letters are now before me, and I<lb/> have particularly
                noted the contents;—with respect to the<lb/> subscribers to the Occident, I will
                endeavor to collect the<lb/> subscriptions as soon as possible &amp; remit you the
                amount:<lb/> with respect to the Institute which we are endeavoring to<lb/>
                establish here, I am afraid it will come to nothing, for<lb/> our Brethren here as
                you correctly state are indeed 'rude and<lb/> uneducated,' and are also tainted with
                infidelity, bigotry<lb/> and superstition;—We have a constantly
                    <sic>encreasing</sic> Jewish<lb/> population, nearly numbering 3,500 but they
                are not of the right<lb/> sort, a moiety<add>?</add> of them being more willing to
                receive assistance<lb/> than to assist or lend their support to either of the
                two<lb/> Congregations; <del>or</del> for educational purposes;—but at the same time
                must give them credit for being Charitable; for calls<lb/> of that nature are indeed
                numerous; as a specimen, upwards<lb/> of $500 was collected from them &amp; the
                societies for the suffering at the <placeName><sic>Pitsburg</sic></placeName>
                fire;—when your <add>חומש</add> is <sic>compleated</sic> it is probable<lb/> I may
                be able to dispose of a few, if you think proper to send<lb/> them out;—The Occident
                does not appear to the taste of our members,<lb/> a work of the plan of the “Voice
                of Jacob,” or the “Jewish Chronicle”<lb/> would suit much better, <sic>their</sic>
                are several subscribers to those<lb/> works, &amp; they appear to take very much,
                controversial works<lb/> in favor of our Religion are required very much in the
                    <placeName>West</placeName>,<lb/> I am a considerable portion of my time,
                answering different<lb/> text of Scriptures, for Clergymen in various sections of
                the <placeName>Western<lb/> Country</placeName>; brought me by our Israelitish
                Pedlar; a cheap pub-<lb/>-lication of that nature would be very beneficial; as</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>constant struggles are made to obtain converts amongst<lb/> our Brethren;—and those
                Pedlars 'tho honest moral men, are in<lb/> general composed of very illiterate
                Germans, who are not able<lb/> to give an answer to the plainest text;—Your Occident
                is<lb/> calculated for the <hi rend="underline">Rich</hi> and <hi rend="underline"
                    >educated Jew</hi>, <hi rend="underline">not for</hi> the poor<lb/> and
                illiterate Sons of <placeName>Israel</placeName>, who only know that they are
                Jews.<lb/> they want something to warm them up as patriots in a</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>118 South 4th Street. Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)indent(2)">
                <placeName>Pa</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="Note:">The address is written sideways in the center of the page.</p>
            <p>national point of view, as well as to stir up their zeal<lb/> in our holy
                Religion;—we are not as in <placeName>Europe</placeName> writing with<lb/> this word
                of Persecution at our throats;—being on an equality with<lb/> the Gentile, we are
                required to be strong &amp; courageous; and altho' few<lb/> in numbers against the
                    Midianitish<add>?</add> Camp, to sound our 'Trumpets'<lb/> break our 'Pitches,'
                and <hi rend="underline">Proclaim aloud</hi> “The Sword of the Lord<lb/> and of
                    <persName>Gideon</persName>.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yours Sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Joseph Jones<add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
        </body>
